				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">if you have a case where the pointer is read in from a data file, and is thus something it can't determine, then the compiler would have to implement and fall back on strict ABI calling. if the compiler then was happy to trust you to declare all functions with a __stdcall or if it then says __stdcall for everything unless you say __fastcall would be up to the compiler. However how you would know the exact address of a function to put into your data without compiling it all first and having a dummy call to the function so it doesn't get stripped means this basically never actually happens and no compiler would handle it.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

